He’s worked an intriguing angle on the story, following a lowly Welsh side on the verge of financial ruin who become Britain’s first co-operative club in order to turn things around. Bolstered by a new sense of team spirit, the club begins to ascend through the leagues. But soon the dream sours as some players are thought to be more equal than others.
